  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Children between the ages of 3 and 12 years,

          -  DSM-IV (APA, 2000) diagnosis of Autistic Disorder (DSM-IV 299.90),

          -  willingness to follow and maintain a gluten-free-dairy-free-diet for 4 weeks.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  food allergies,

          -  celiac disease,

          -  inflammatory bowel disease,

          -  infectious gastrointestinal,

          -  seizure disorder,

          -  neurological problems with behavioral changes,

          -  unwillingness to undertake the dietary challenge with milk and gluten or to maintain a
             gluten-free-dairy-free-diet during the study were excluded
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
